metadata.name: Walking Sideways - Original
metadata.description:
1/3

Vibrancy, colour, decadence and joy. I never felt any of these for the most part of my childhood.

I was constantly being reminded that there was so much colour and beauty in the world that surrounds me.

My eye however, couldn't see past the gloom and murk that I was made to feel. And these were painted in eerie shades of black.

I was expected to set myself on a path of linearity, instead, I found myself walking sideways.

[High-Resolution file would be provided via contacting me on Twitter DM](https://twitter.com/citrineandmint)

P.S - I have hidden a small easter-egg in the High-Res File.
